OL,7,FShaun, 37, works full-time and says he
OL,8,Fdepends on the #500 he receives every
OL,9,Fmonth in Personal Independence
OL,10,FPayments (PIP) to pay for a specially-
OL,11,Fadapted car.
OL,13,FShaun lost his leg below the knee at
OL,14,Fthe age of two after a tractor
OL,15,Fincident and took up cricket at the
OL,16,Fage of 7.
OL,18,FHe says he is only able to play
OL,19,Fcricket whilst on a lot of painkillers
OL,20,Fand that often he is in a lot of pain
OL,21,Fwhilst playing the sport.
